        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 2:05PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 204 PM CDT/304 PM EDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Roselawn, or near Lake Village, moving southeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny to nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wheatfield, Thayer, Roselawn, Lake Dalecarlia, Hanging Grove, Brook,
Stoutsburg, Foresman, DeMotte, Fair Oaks, Dunns Bridge, Hebron,
Remington, Wadena, Kouts, Boone Grove, Sumava Resorts, Baileys
Corner, Mount Ayr, Goodland, Parr, Lowell, Schneider, Shelby, and
Lake Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
